Subject: RE: [T2] Stuck rings

Another thing that the Corvair folks
http://www.corvaircenter.com/forum/index.html do is pour a chemical
manufactured by Berryman's http://www.berrymanproducts.com/. I think its
Berryman's B-12. I think they pour it directly into the cylinders to unstick
rings. Pour it in, let it sit, blow it out, and crank it up. 

You should change the oil afterwards. I'm sure that these solvents will thin
the oil.

Steve 




